In response to the fast - growing number of publications about this newly developed disease, this article tried to give a timely and comprehensive review of the subject of rapid development.
We'll discuss the basics of epidemiology, etyology, virology, diagnosis, treatment, prognosis, and disease prevention.
Although many questions remain unanswered, we hope that this review will help us to understand and eradicate this threatening disease.
