The virus was highly homologous with the coronavirus (CoV) which caused the outbreak of acute respiratory syndrome in 2003; therefore, it was named SARS-CoV-2 by the World Health Organization (WHO) on February 11, 2020, and the disease caused by which it was called CoV Disease-19 (COVID-19).
