WHO warns that COVID-19 is "enemy public number 1" and potentially destructive more powerful than terrorism.
According to PubMed (https://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/), in less than two months since the first report on January 7th 2020 that established the sequence of viruses isolated from some patients, more than 200 papers were published about COVID-19, which included virology, epidemiology, etyology, diagnosis, and treatment.
This review is trying to summarize the progress of research in the field of this fast - growing new subject.
Whenever possible, we will try to compare COVID-19 with SARS and other CoV diseases, which are called Middle Eastern respiratory syndrome (MERS, outbreaks in 2012).
We will also discuss matters that have been learned so far regarding prevention and prognosis of disease as well as some other unanswered questions but urgent.
